org.jppf.utils.collections

Class AbstractCollectionMap<K,V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jppf.utils.collections.AbstractCollectionMap<K,V>
  • Type Parameters:
    K - the type of keys in the map.
    V - the type of values in the collections mapped to the keys.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Iterable<V>, CollectionMap<K,V>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AbstractCollectionConcurrentMap, AbstractCollectionHashtable, AbstractCollectionSortedMap, ArrayListHashMap, EnumSetEnumMap, SetHashMap, SetIdentityMap

    public abstract class AbstractCollectionMap<K,V>
extends Object
implements CollectionMap<K,V>
    A map whose values are collections of a given component type.
